# Form Validation Pattern

This project uses **vee-validate + Yup** with custom form field wrapper components.

## Form Field Components

Located in `src/components/common/form/`. All are auto-imported.

| Component | PrimeVue Base | Purpose |
|---|---|---|
| `BaseField` | — | Layout wrapper (label, error, help text, aria) |
| `InputTextField` | `InputText` | Text input |
| `InputNumberField` | `InputNumber` | Number input |
| `InputMaskField` | `InputMask` | Masked input |
| `PasswordField` | `Password` | Password input |
| `TextareaField` | `Textarea` | Multiline text |
| `SelectField` | `Select` | Dropdown select |
| `MultiSelectField` | `MultiSelect` | Multi-select |
| `CheckboxField` | `Checkbox` | Checkbox |
| `RadioField` | `RadioButton` | Radio button |
| `ToggleSwitchField` | `ToggleSwitch` | Toggle switch |
| `DatePickerField` | `DatePicker` | Date picker |
| `EditorField` | `Editor` | Rich text editor |

## Field Component Props Pattern

All field wrappers share a common interface:

```typescript
interface Props {
  modelValue?: FieldValueType  // v-model value
  name: string                 // Field name (used as id + form binding)
  label?: string               // Label text
  placeholder?: string         // Placeholder text
  helpText?: string            // Help text below field
  error?: string | null        // Validation error message
  disabled?: boolean
  readonly?: boolean
  required?: boolean           // Shows * indicator on label
  size?: FieldSize             // 'small' | 'large' | undefined
}
```

## Usage Pattern

Field wrappers handle layout, error display, and accessibility. Pass error from Yup validation:

```vue
<template>
  <form @submit.prevent="handleSubmit">
    <InputTextField
      v-model="form.userID"
      name="userID"
      :label="t('login.userId')"
      :error="errors.userID"
      required
    />
    <PasswordField
      v-model="form.password"
      name="password"
      :label="t('login.password')"
      :error="errors.password"
      required
    />
    <Button type="submit" :label="t('login.submit')" />
  </form>
</template>
```

## Yup Schema Pattern

### Shared schemas in `src/schemas/`

```typescript
import * as Yup from 'yup'

export const loginSchema = Yup.object({
  userID: Yup.string()
    .trim()
    .required('User ID is required')
    .min(3, 'User ID must be at least 3 characters'),
  password: Yup.string()
    .required('Password is required')
    .min(6, 'Password must be at least 6 characters'),
})
```

### Module-specific schemas in `src/modules/<name>/schemas/`

### Reusable validation test functions in `src/schemas/rules.ts`

```typescript
// Usage: Yup.string().test('strong-password', 'Error message', isStrongPassword)
export function isStrongPassword(value: string | undefined): boolean { ... }
export function isValidPhone(value: string | undefined): boolean { ... }
```

### Error extraction utility in `src/schemas/rules.ts`

```typescript
import { extractYupErrors } from '@/schemas/rules'

try {
  await schema.validate(formData, { abortEarly: false })
} catch (error) {
  const { fieldErrors } = extractYupErrors(error)
  // fieldErrors = { userID: 'User ID is required', password: '...' }
}
```

## Rules

- **ALWAYS** use the `*Field` wrapper components instead of raw PrimeVue inputs in forms
- **ALWAYS** use `BaseField` as the layout wrapper when creating new field components
- Pass `error` prop from Yup validation to display error messages
- Use `extractYupErrors()` to convert Yup errors into a `Record<string, string>` for field binding
- Schema files use `Yup.object({...})` pattern — import Yup as `import * as Yup from 'yup'`
- Shared rules go in `src/schemas/rules.ts`, module-specific schemas go in `src/modules/<name>/schemas/`
